{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":13843,"record_hash":"sha256:c330fc69e22aefd1aa80832e5f097c543e96c85929c2d15da284f6b1ef9ee8ce","timestamp":"2026-05-09T17:25:59.837Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"user","text":"PLEASE IMPLEMENT THIS PLAN:\n# Agentlog Shareable Session Data Shape Plan\n\n## Summary\nReshape the POC so captured agent sessions are durable, project-scoped, and shareable-ready, while the command remains hidden, explicit-path only, project-targeted, and non-pushing/non-serializing.\n\nDo not use `meta:local:*` for the main session data. GitMeta treats that namespace as never serialized, and these sessions are meant to support future handoff and colleague sharing. Use `gitbutler:*` keys instead.\n\n## Key Changes\n- Add `agent-session-capture/future-use-cases.md` describing:\n  - Session handoff across machines and agents.\n  - Sharing session details with colleagues through a future GitButler web view.\n  - Many-to-many relationships: one session can relate to many branches/PRs, and one branch/PR can relate to many sessions.\n- Update existing docs to say:\n  - POC writes shareable-ready `gitbutler:*` keys, not `meta:local:*`.\n  - Capture does not serialize, push, fetch, or sync GitMeta yet.\n  - All stored agentlog values are redacted before writing.\n  - Branch/PR/commit links are future references to durable project sessions, not owners of session data.\n\n## Storage Shape\nUse the `project` GitMeta target by default.\n\nSession index:\n\n```text\ngitbutler:agent-sessions = set<session-key>\n```\n\nDurable session prefix:\n\n```text\ngitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:*\n```\n\nFor this POC, derive `session-key` deterministically from the current source:\n\n```text\nsha256(agent + NUL + provider-session-id)\n```\n\nor, if no provider session id exists:\n\n```text\nsha256(agent + NUL + canonical-transcript-path-bytes)\n```\n\nSession-level keys:\n\n```text\n:schema = gitbutler.agent-session.v1\n:updated-at = <capture timestamp>\n:sources = set<source-key>\n:record-hashes = set<sha256:record>\n:transcript = list<TranscriptEnvelope JSON>\n```\n\nSource-level keys:\n\n```text\n:source:<source-key>:agent\n:source:<source-key>:provider\n:source:<source-key>:model\n:source:<source-key>:tool-version\n:source:<source-key>:provider-session-key\n:source:<source-key>:source-name\n:source:<source-key>:source-size\n:source:<source-key>:source-sha256\n:source:<source-key>:last-record-index\n:source:<source-key>:captured-at\n```\n\nDo not store full transcript paths, cwd, or git branch in this POC data shape. `source-name` is basename only. `provider-session-key` is hashed, never raw.\n\n## Transcript Envelope\nKeep one ordered `:transcript` list per durable GitButler session. Each list item is one redacted JSON envelope with only per-record data.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"schema\": \"gitbutler.agent-transcript.v1\",\n  \"source_key\": \"sha256-...\",\n  \"record_index\": 0,\n  \"record_hash\": \"sha256:...\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"...\",\n  \"event_kind\": \"...\",\n  \"event_category\": \"message\",\n  \"role\": \"user\",\n  \"content_text\": \"redacted normalized text when easy to extract\",\n  \"tool_name\": null,\n  \"source_record\": {}\n}\n```\n\nRules:\n- `content_text` is the normalized conversation message body.\n- Omit repeated session/source metadata from each envelope; use `source_key` to join back to source keys.\n- Omit `cwd`, `git_branch`, provider session ids, message ids, parent ids, turn ids, and redaction counters from top-level envelope fields.\n- Keep redacted `source_record` for provenance and future normalization improvements.\n- `event_category`: `session`, `context`, `message`, `tool`, or `other`.\n- Extract `content_text` and `tool_name` only from obvious Codex/Claude fields.\n- Redact every copied string field and the full `source_record` before writing.\n\n## Future Association Model\nDo not implement branch/PR/commit associations in this POC.\n\nLater, when GitButler has an explicit target, write relationship references like:\n\n```text\n<branch/change/commit target>\n  gitbutler:agent-sessions = set<session-key>\n```\n\nThis supports:\n- one session contributing to multiple branches/PRs\n- multiple sessions contributing to one branch/PR\n- sessions that exist before any code or branch association\n\n## Test Plan\n- `cargo test -p but-agentlog`\n  - session index is written under `gitbutler:agent-sessions`\n  - session data is under `gitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:*`\n  - no `meta:local:gitbutler:agent-session:*` keys are written\n  - source-level keys are written with basename-only `source-name`\n  - transcript envelopes contain only the slim per-record fields\n  - envelope `source_key` joins to source metadata\n  - repeat capture remains idempotent\n  - growing transcript appends only new records\n  - missing transcript list still backfills from existing record hashes\n  - redaction applies to source metadata, normalized envelope fields, and `source_record`\n- `cargo check -p but --features agentlog`\n- `cargo fmt --check`\n- `cargo clippy -p but-agentlog --all-targets --no-deps`\n\n## Assumptions\n- All stored agentlog data is intended to be shareable eventually, so all stored values must be redacted before saving.\n- The POC still does not share data because it does not call GitMeta serialize, push, fetch, or sync.\n- `project` remains the default target.\n- Standard `agent:*` keys are deferred until there is an interoperability/publish contract.\n- Cross-agent continuation is enabled by the durable project session model, but joining multiple provider sessions into one GitButler session waits for a later explicit UX.\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-09T17:25:59.837Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"user","content":[{"type":"input_text","text":"PLEASE IMPLEMENT THIS PLAN:\n# Agentlog Shareable Session Data Shape Plan\n\n## Summary\nReshape the POC so captured agent sessions are durable, project-scoped, and shareable-ready, while the command remains hidden, explicit-path only, project-targeted, and non-pushing/non-serializing.\n\nDo not use `meta:local:*` for the main session data. GitMeta treats that namespace as never serialized, and these sessions are meant to support future handoff and colleague sharing. Use `gitbutler:*` keys instead.\n\n## Key Changes\n- Add `agent-session-capture/future-use-cases.md` describing:\n  - Session handoff across machines and agents.\n  - Sharing session details with colleagues through a future GitButler web view.\n  - Many-to-many relationships: one session can relate to many branches/PRs, and one branch/PR can relate to many sessions.\n- Update existing docs to say:\n  - POC writes shareable-ready `gitbutler:*` keys, not `meta:local:*`.\n  - Capture does not serialize, push, fetch, or sync GitMeta yet.\n  - All stored agentlog values are redacted before writing.\n  - Branch/PR/commit links are future references to durable project sessions, not owners of session data.\n\n## Storage Shape\nUse the `project` GitMeta target by default.\n\nSession index:\n\n```text\ngitbutler:agent-sessions = set<session-key>\n```\n\nDurable session prefix:\n\n```text\ngitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:*\n```\n\nFor this POC, derive `session-key` deterministically from the current source:\n\n```text\nsha256(agent + NUL + provider-session-id)\n```\n\nor, if no provider session id exists:\n\n```text\nsha256(agent + NUL + canonical-transcript-path-bytes)\n```\n\nSession-level keys:\n\n```text\n:schema = gitbutler.agent-session.v1\n:updated-at = <capture timestamp>\n:sources = set<source-key>\n:record-hashes = set<sha256:record>\n:transcript = list<TranscriptEnvelope JSON>\n```\n\nSource-level keys:\n\n```text\n:source:<source-key>:agent\n:source:<source-key>:provider\n:source:<source-key>:model\n:source:<source-key>:tool-version\n:source:<source-key>:provider-session-key\n:source:<source-key>:source-name\n:source:<source-key>:source-size\n:source:<source-key>:source-sha256\n:source:<source-key>:last-record-index\n:source:<source-key>:captured-at\n```\n\nDo not store full transcript paths, cwd, or git branch in this POC data shape. `source-name` is basename only. `provider-session-key` is hashed, never raw.\n\n## Transcript Envelope\nKeep one ordered `:transcript` list per durable GitButler session. Each list item is one redacted JSON envelope with only per-record data.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"schema\": \"gitbutler.agent-transcript.v1\",\n  \"source_key\": \"sha256-...\",\n  \"record_index\": 0,\n  \"record_hash\": \"sha256:...\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"...\",\n  \"event_kind\": \"...\",\n  \"event_category\": \"message\",\n  \"role\": \"user\",\n  \"content_text\": \"redacted normalized text when easy to extract\",\n  \"tool_name\": null,\n  \"source_record\": {}\n}\n```\n\nRules:\n- `content_text` is the normalized conversation message body.\n- Omit repeated session/source metadata from each envelope; use `source_key` to join back to source keys.\n- Omit `cwd`, `git_branch`, provider session ids, message ids, parent ids, turn ids, and redaction counters from top-level envelope fields.\n- Keep redacted `source_record` for provenance and future normalization improvements.\n- `event_category`: `session`, `context`, `message`, `tool`, or `other`.\n- Extract `content_text` and `tool_name` only from obvious Codex/Claude fields.\n- Redact every copied string field and the full `source_record` before writing.\n\n## Future Association Model\nDo not implement branch/PR/commit associations in this POC.\n\nLater, when GitButler has an explicit target, write relationship references like:\n\n```text\n<branch/change/commit target>\n  gitbutler:agent-sessions = set<session-key>\n```\n\nThis supports:\n- one session contributing to multiple branches/PRs\n- multiple sessions contributing to one branch/PR\n- sessions that exist before any code or branch association\n\n## Test Plan\n- `cargo test -p but-agentlog`\n  - session index is written under `gitbutler:agent-sessions`\n  - session data is under `gitbutler:agent-session:<session-key>:*`\n  - no `meta:local:gitbutler:agent-session:*` keys are written\n  - source-level keys are written with basename-only `source-name`\n  - transcript envelopes contain only the slim per-record fields\n  - envelope `source_key` joins to source metadata\n  - repeat capture remains idempotent\n  - growing transcript appends only new records\n  - missing transcript list still backfills from existing record hashes\n  - redaction applies to source metadata, normalized envelope fields, and `source_record`\n- `cargo check -p but --features agentlog`\n- `cargo fmt --check`\n- `cargo clippy -p but-agentlog --all-targets --no-deps`\n\n## Assumptions\n- All stored agentlog data is intended to be shareable eventually, so all stored values must be redacted before saving.\n- The POC still does not share data because it does not call GitMeta serialize, push, fetch, or sync.\n- `project` remains the default target.\n- Standard `agent:*` keys are deferred until there is an interoperability/publish contract.\n- Cross-agent continuation is enabled by the durable project session model, but joining multiple provider sessions into one GitButler session waits for a later explicit UX.\n"}]}}}